  "instructions": [
    "Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a wok over medium-high heat.",
    "Add 1 pound of beef or pork and cook until browned, breaking it up into small pieces as it cooks.",
    "Add 1 cup of chopped onion, 2 carrots, and 2 stalks of celery, and cook until the vegetables are softened.",
    "Add 2 cups of beef broth, 1 cup of wine, 1 cup of sour cream, and 1 cup of crushed egg yolks, and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook until the sauce has thickened, stirring occasionally.",
    "Season the sauce with 1 teaspoon of kosher salt and 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper.",
    "Add 1 cup of chopped scallions and 1/4 cup of chopped cilantro to the sauce and stir to combine.",
    "To assemble the gyoza, lay an egg roll wrapper on a clean surface and place a tablespoon of the filling in the center of the wrapper.",
    "Brush the edges of the wrapper with water and fold the wrapper into a triangle, pressing the edges together to seal the gyoza.",
    "Heat 2 tablespoons of sesame oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add a few of the gyoza to the skillet and cook until the bottoms are golden brown.",
    "Add 1 cup of water to the skillet and cover with a lid.",
    "Steam the gyoza for 5-7 minutes, or until the filling is cooked through and the wrappers are tender.",
    "Serve the gyoza hot with a dipping sauce made from 1 tablespoon of floral honey, 1 tablespoon of raw honey, and 2 tablespoons of lemon juice.",
    "Garnish with chopped green onions and chopped cilantro, if desired.",
    "Serve the gyoza with a side of kimchi sauce, made from 1 cup of fermented kimchi, 1/4 cup of chopped scallions, and 1/4 cup of chopped cilantro, if desired."
  ],
